definition.value: A galactosyl group obtained by removing the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of beta-D-galactose and, by extension, of a lower oligosaccharide having galactose at the reducing end. The unsubstituted parent of the class of beta-D-galactosyl groups.
A 1-alkyl-2-acylglycerol having acetyl as the acyl substituent.
